# Implementation Workflow

## Output Order

1. Brief clarification (problem, expected behavior)
2. Scenario summary (normal flow, edge cases)
3. Implementation
4. **Tests** (unit + E2E if applicable)
5. Key notes

## Doc and Test Sync (MANDATORY)

On every change, check whether these need updates:

- `docs/design/` - design doc (formulas, attributes, UI specs); see [index.md](docs/design/index.md); UI tokens: [11-ui-tokens.md](docs/design/11-ui-tokens.md)
- `docs/requirements-format.md` - acceptance criteria, user stories
- Unit tests: `frontend/src/**/*.spec.js`
- E2E tests: `e2e/browser/*.spec.js`

Update them when the change affects formulas, attributes, UI behavior, or acceptance criteria.

**Design change impact**: When modifying core flows (squad, recruitment, skills, intro, routing), run the [Design Change Impact Checklist](docs/design-change-impact.md) to avoid UI/flow oversights (e.g., Examples, E2E, routing).

## Color Usage (Gold)

- `var(--color-gold)` / gold color: **ONLY** for gold-related content (currency, rewards, sell, costs)
- Other highlights (accent, level-up, skill, victory): use `var(--accent)`, `var(--color-exp)`, `var(--color-skill)`, `var(--color-victory)` etc.

## Tooltip Style (Unified)

All hover tips must use the custom tooltip pattern, not native `title`:

- Wrap: `class="tooltip-wrap has-tip"` (has-tip adds dotted underline and help cursor)
- Content: `<span class="tooltip-text">Tip content here</span>` inside the wrap
- Do NOT use `:title` or `title=` for user-facing tooltips; it shows native OS style

## Prohibited

- Non-ASCII in code
- Skipping tests for core logic
- Using `&&` in PowerShell (use `;` instead)
- Overengineering, placeholder logic

## E2E Definition

- E2E = full UI flow through browser to backend
- Location: `e2e/browser/`
- Use Playwright

## E2E Port Release (Before Running)

Before running `npm run e2e`, release ports 8080 and 5173 and reset DB:

```powershell
powershell -ExecutionPolicy Bypass -File scripts/release-e2e-ports.ps1
```

The `e2e` npm script runs this automatically. The script also clears `test-results` and resets `text-idle.db` for a fresh run. If running e2e manually or ports are in use, run the script first.

## Anti-Hang Execution Mode

To reduce "stuck" behavior during long operations, use this execution style by default:

- Prefer short, single-purpose commands over large command batches
- Run long tasks in background and poll output every 3-5 seconds
- Send a brief progress update at least every 10 seconds during long tasks
- Read only log tail sections (for example, last 100-200 lines), not full large files
- If no new output appears for 30+ seconds, report current status and next action
- If ports are required (for example 8080/5173), verify port state before and after task start
